---
import Page from "../layouts/Page.astro";

const EMAIL = "prasad.rajeshwar@gmail.com";
---

<Page
  title="Privacy Policy — Useless Today"
  description="The Useless Today privacy policy: what little data we store (theme preference and a local click counter), how we handle external links, and how to contact us."
  path="/privacy/"
  eyebrow="Legal"
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  intro="We built Useless Today to waste time, not to collect yours. This policy explains the little data the site touches and how we handle it — in plain English."
  updated="22 June 2026"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy describes how Useless Today ("we", "us", or "our")
    handles information when you visit
    <a href="https://uselesstoday.com/">uselesstoday.com</a> (the "Site"). By
    using the Site, you agree to the practices described here.
  </p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>
    We don't ask you to create an account, and we don't ask for your name,
    email, or any personal details to use the Site. The only things stored are
    kept in your own browser to make the Site work the way you'd expect.
  </p>

  <h2>Information stored in your browser</h2>
  <p>
    Useless Today uses your browser's <strong>local storage</strong> — not
    cookies — for two small, purely functional purposes:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Theme preference.</strong> If you switch between light and dark mode, we remember your choice so the Site looks right next time.</li>
    <li><strong>Time-wasted counter.</strong> We keep a small per-day tally of how many useless links you've opened, so the on-screen counter can show it. This number lives only on your device.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This information never leaves your browser, is not linked to your identity,
    and you can clear it at any time through your browser settings.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics</h2>
  <p>
    We may use privacy-friendly, aggregate analytics to understand how many
    people visit the Site and which useless websites are popular. Where we do,
    we aim to use tools that do not track individuals across the web or build
    advertising profiles. We do not sell your data — we don't even collect
    enough to sell.
  </p>

  <h2>External links</h2>
  <p>
    The whole point of Useless Today is to send you to other websites. When you
    click a link on the wall or hit <strong>Surprise me</strong>, you leave our
    Site and land on a third-party site we don't control. Those sites have their
    own privacy practices, and this policy does not cover them. We curate links
    in good faith but can't be responsible for what other sites do with your
    information.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    The Site is intended for a general audience and does not knowingly collect
    personal information from anyone, including children.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we'll
    revise the "Last updated" date above. Continued use of the Site after a
    change means you accept the updated policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about privacy? Email us at
    <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}>{EMAIL}</a> or visit our
    <a href="/contact/">Contact page</a>.
  </p>
</Page>
